    • Uses of JCLEC in net.sf.jclec.problem.classification.algorithm.bojarczuk

      Classes in net.sf.jclec.problem.classification.algorithm.bojarczuk that implement JCLEC 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  BojarczukAlgorithm
      Classifier algorithm for Bojarczuk et al. 2004 - A constrained-syntax genetic programming system for discovering classification rules: application to medical data sets The Bojarczuk et al. algorithm performs mutation and reproduction to evolve rules whose consequent is evaluated for each of the data classes.
      class  BojarczukEvaluator
      Evaluator for Bojarczuk et al. 2004 - A constrained-syntax genetic programming system for discovering classification rules: application to medical data sets The fitness function evaluates the confusion matrix for each of the data classes.
      class  BojarczukSyntaxTreeSpecies
      Species for Bojarczuk et al. 2004 - A constrained-syntax genetic programming system for discovering classification rules: application to medical data sets Defines the grammar, the production rules, the terminal and non-terminal symbols to generate the classification rules.

    • Uses of JCLEC in net.sf.jclec.problem.classification.algorithm.tan

      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  TanAlgorithm
      Classifier Algorithm for Tan et al. 2002 - Mining multiple comprehensible classification rules using genetic programming The Tan et al. algorithm performs reproduction, recombination and mutation, keeping an elite population.
      class  TanClassifier
      Classifier for Tan et al. 2002 - Mining multiple comprehensible classification rules using genetic programming The Tan et al. algorithm states that the rules within the classifier must be sorted according to their specificity value.
      class  TanEvaluator
      Evaluator for Tan et al. 2002 - Mining multiple comprehensible classification rules using genetic programming The fitness function evaluates the confusion matrix for the data class of the current algorithm' execution.
      class  TanSyntaxTreeSpecies
      Species for Tan et al. 2002 - Mining multiple comprehensible classification rules using genetic programming Defines the grammar, the production rules, the terminal and non-terminal symbols to generate the classification rules.
